'''Erick Guerrero''' is an associate professor at the [[University of Southern California School of Social Work|University of Southern California, Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work]] with a courtesy appointment at the Marshall School of Business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dworakpeck.usc.edu/research/research-projects/social-change-and-innovation|title=Social Change and Innovation {{!}} Research Projects {{!}} USC Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work|website=dworakpeck.usc.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Guerrero grew up in Mexico City and currently works and lives in Los Angeles, CA with his wife and daughter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Erick_Guerrero|title=Erick G. Guerrero {{!}} MA, PhD {{!}} University of Southern California, California {{!}} USC {{!}} Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work & Marshall School of Business {{!}} ResearchGate|website=ResearchGate|language=en|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref>


== Education ==
Guerrero obtained a degree clinical psychology at the [[Universidad de las Américas, A.C.|Universidad de las Americas]] in Mexico City and his PhD in social work in management at the [[University of Chicago]]. Trained as an organizational and implementation scientist, his program of research focuses on three inter-related areas associated with improving standards of care for vulnerable populations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://attcniatx.blogspot.com/2017/10/cultural-competence-and-organizational.html|title=The ATTC/NIATx Service Improvement Blog: Cultural competence and organizational change: Meet the researcher, Dr. Erick Guerrero|website=The ATTC/NIATx Service Improvement Blog|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref>

== Career ==
Dr. Guerrero would eventually receive the tenure as an Associate Professor from the [[University of Southern California School of Social Work|University of Southern California, Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Erick_Guerrero|title=Erick G. Guerrero {{!}} MA, PhD {{!}} University of Southern California, California {{!}} USC {{!}} Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work & Marshall School of Business {{!}} ResearchGate|website=ResearchGate|language=en|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref> Guerrero has been expanding the scope of his research studies to implementation of evidence-based practices in different health care areas. Most recently, Dr. Guerrero heads the team of Integrated Substance Abuse Treatment to Eliminate Disparities for the [[University of Southern California School of Social Work|University of Southern California, Suzanne Dworak-Peck School of Social Work]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.isated.com/|title=iSATed research team based in USC school of social work in Los Angeles|website=iSATed|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref>

He spent 13 years providing domestic violence and substance abuse counseling in Chicago <ref>https://dworakpeck.usc.edu/news/going-big-erick-guerrero-changing-systems-to-make-getting-substance-abuse-treatment-easier</ref> This experience led him to obtaining a Ph.D. in macro social work, writing more than 50 articles in this area.<ref>http://profiles.sc-ctsi.org/erick.guerrero</ref> He also leads innovative research on organizational capacity to improve delivery of health care for underserved populations.<ref>(https://dworakpeck.usc.edu/news/how-managers-health-care-organizations-drive-innovation</ref> He has developed the evidence to inform manager's practices to achieve results for clients from ethnic minority backgrounds. His influential scholarship in management and health care has been acknowledged by several organizations.<ref>https://dworakpeck.usc.edu/news/guerrero-receives-fellowship-award-for-social-work-management-research</ref>

Dr. Guerrero is one of few scholars in social work management with a highly funded research agenda to train new investigators and conduct large studies in health care.<ref>http://www.isated.com</ref>

