"'''Inside the Ivory Tower'''" is a [[College and university rankings|ranking]] of the world's best [[university]] programs in [[international relations]]. The ranking is published by the ''[[Foreign Policy]]'' magazine in collaboration with the Teaching, Research, and International Policy (TRIP) Project at the [[College of William & Mary]]. The survey is based on input from "all international relations scholars employed at a college or university who have an affiliation with a political science department or school of public policy and who teach or conduct research on issues that cross international borders."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trip.wm.edu/home/index.php/surveys/faculty-survey|title=Faculty Survey|last=|first=|date=2014|website=TRIP|language=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>
The first TRIP Faculty Survey was conducted in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wmpeople.wm.edu/asset/index/smpete/insidetheivorytower2005|title=Inside the Ivory Tower|last=Peterson|first=Susan|last2=Maliniak|first2=Dan|date=|website=Foreign Policy|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=|last3=Tierney|first3=Michael}}</ref> One of the questions asked respondents to rank International Relations graduate schools in the U.S. The survey has since expanded to include undergraduate programs.<ref name="AllPubs">{{cite web|title=Academic Publications |url=https://trip.wm.edu/home/index.php/publications |work=Institute for the Theory and Practice of International Relations, TRIP |publisher=College of William & Mary |accessdate=12 December 2017 |df= }}</ref> The survey began including universities outside of the U.S. in 2009.<ref name="ivorytower">{{cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2009/10/15/inside-the-ivory-tower/|title=Inside the Ivory Tower|author1=Daniel Maliniak|author2=Amy Oakes|date=March–April 2009|work=[[Foreign Policy]]|publisher=[[The Slate Group]]|accessdate=20 December 2017|author3=Susan Peterson|author4=Michael J. Tierney}}</ref> The survey was last conducted in 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/02/20/top-fifty-schools-international-relations-foreign-policy/|title=The Best International Relations Schools in the World|website=Foreign Policy|language=en|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> and asks the respondents to rank the top five international relations programs by degree level. The rankings are determined by the percentage of respondents who list a particular school.<ref>https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/02/20/top-fifty-schools-international-relations-foreign-policy/</ref>
