{{unreferenced|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox school | name = Modern Montessori School | image = [[File:MMS LOGO.png]] | established = 1985 | type = Private school | city = [[Amman]] | state = | country = [[Jordan]] | campus = 24,000 square meters | enrollment = | faculty = | SAT = | ACT = | athletics = | athletics_conference = | homepage = http://www.montessori.edu.jo }}
The '''Modern Montessori School''' (MMS) is a private school in [[Amman]], [[Jordan]] founded by Randa Amin Hasan. It caters to students from 3–18 years old, and is affiliated with the [[International Baccalaureate]] [http://www.ibo.org/school/001076/] and accredited by the International Centre for Montessori Education (ICME)[http://www.montessori-icme.com]. It was established in 1985 and is built on a 24,000 m2 piece of land. It is designed to meet international standards in school requirements. It offers a [[Montessori]] Early Childhood Education Programme from Nursery 1 to KG2; bilingual English/Arabic curriculum for grades 1-8; a specially formulated pre-IB Bridge Years (BYP) curriculum for grades 9 + 10; and IB curriculum for grades 11 + 12. This school is recognized by the International Baccalaureate Organization as a full IB school. It offers the PYP system for grades 1-5 and the MYP system for grades 6-10 and finally the IB diploma for grades 11 and 12.
Its students and administration hold an annual Model Arab League conference ("AMAL") as well as other yearly conferences, events, and seminars.
